Description: Round-topped limestone stela of Sahathor with two wedjat-eyes at the top flanked by columns of Hieroglyphic text including a cartouche of a King Ibia; below are fourteen rows of Hieroglyphic text; representation of the deceased and wife in the bottom left-hand corner.
Curator's comments: Published: HTBM 4: Plate 27 PM I Part 2: p.807 Bourriau, Pharaohs and Mortals, no. 45
Acquisition name: Purchased from: R J Moss & Co
